lant, to the families who struggled with the shortage of housing and services. Thematically organized and closely focused, Magnetic Mountain signals the beginning of a new stage in the writing of Soviet social history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCommunismzSoviet UnionvCase studies. 0aCommunismzSoviet UnionxCase studies. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  ablast furnace.  acapitalism.  acold war.  acommunism.  adictator.  aeastern europe.  aeuropean history.  afactory workers.  ahistory.  aindustrialization.  airon plant.  akotkin.  alabor.  amarxism.  ametal.  anonfiction.  apolitical science.  apolitical system.  apolitics.  arussia.  arussian history.  arussian revolution.  arussian soviet history.  asocial change.  asocial history.  asocialism.  asoviet history.  asoviet steel.  asoviet studies.  asoviet union.  astalin.  astalinism.  asteel plant.  aussr.  aworkers.  aworking class.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091885640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520918856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520918856/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles